{"title_page": "Demographics of Bangladesh", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=April 2018}}  \n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}} \n{{Infobox country demographics\n|country            = Bangladesh\n|image              = File:Bangladesch Bev\u00f6lkerungsdichte 2011.svg\n|caption            = Map showing the population density of each district in Bangladesh.\n|size_of_population = {{UN Population|Bangladesh}} (2016 est.) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unfpa.org/data/world-population/BD|title=UNFPA - United Nations Population Fund|website=Unfpa.org|accessdate=23 June 2019}}</ref>\n|growth             = 1% (2017 est.)<ref name=\"CIA World Factbook 2017\">{{cite web |title=The World Factbook: Bangladesh: People and Society |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/bg.html#People |publisher=Central Intelligence Agency |accessdate=26 April 2018}}</ref>\n|birth              = 18.80 births/1,000 <br />population (2017 est.)<ref name=\"CIA World Factbook 2017\" />\n|death              = 5.40 deaths/1,000 <br />population (2017 est.)<ref name=\"CIA World Factbook 2017\" />\n|life               = 72.7 years (2018)<ref name=\"CIA World Factbook 2017\" />\n|life_male          = 71.1 years\n|life_female        = 74.4 years\n|fertility          = 2.17  children born/woman <br />(2017 est.)<ref name=\"CIA World Factbook 2017\" />\n|infant_mortality   = 31.70 deaths/1,000 live births <br />(2017 est.)<ref name=\"CIA World Factbook 2017\" />\n|age_0-14_years     = 27.76 (2017 est.)<ref name=\"CIA World Factbook 2017\" />\n|age_15-64_years    = 66.02\n|age_65_years = 6.23\n| total_mf_ratio    =  0.97 male(s)/female<br />(2017 est.)<ref name=\"CIA World Factbook 2017\" />\n| sr_at_birth       = 1.04 male(s)/female\n| sr_under_15       = 1.03 male(s)/female\n| sr_15\u201364_years    = 0.91 male(s)/female\n| sr_65_years_over  = 0.97 male(s)/female\n|nation             = [[Bangladeshi]]\n|major_ethnic       = [[Bengali people|Bengali]]\n|minor_ethnic       = [[Chakma people|Chakma]], <br /> [[Marma people|Marma]],<br />[[Mundas]],<br />[[Garo (tribe)|Garos (Achiks)]],<br /> [[Oraons]], <br />[[Santal|Santhals]],<br />[[Mru people (Mrucha)|Mro]],<br /> [[Bisnupriya Manipuri Society|Manipuri]],<br />[[Zomi]], [[Bihari people|Bihari]] ([[Stranded Pakistani]])\n|official           = [[Bengali language|Bengali]]\n|spoken             = [[Bengali language|Bengali]], [[Chittagonian language]], [[Sylheti]], [[Santali language|Santali]], [[Chakma language|Chakma]], [[Kokborok|Tripuri]], [[Khasi language|Khasi]], [[Mundari language|Mundari]]\n}}\n{{Bengalis}} \n[[Bangladesh]] is the [[List of countries by population|eighth-most populated]] country in the world with almost 2.2% of the [[World population|world's population]]. According to {{UN Population|source}}, the population stood at {{UN Population|Bangladesh}} in 2016.\n\n[[Bangladesh]] (Previously [[East Pakistan]] between 1947 and 1971 and [[East Bengal]] before 1947) is largely [[Ethnic group|ethnically]] homogeneous, and its name derives from the [[Bengali people|Bengali]] ethno-linguistic group which comprises 98% of the [[Bangladeshi people|population]]. The [[Chittagong Hill Tracts]], [[Sylhet]], [[Mymensingh]] and [[Rajshahi Division|North Bengal]] divisions are home to diverse [[Indigenous peoples in Bangladesh|indigenous peoples]]. There are many dialects of Bengali spoken throughout the region. The dialect spoken by those in [[Chittagong]] and Sylhet are particularly distinctive. The population is estimated at {{#expr:{{replace|{{UN_Population|Bangladesh}}|,||}}/1e6 round 0}} million ({{UN_Population|Year}}{{UN_Population|ref}}). About 89% of Bangladeshis are Muslims, followed by Hindus (10\n.7%), Buddhists (0.6%) and Christians (0.4%) and others.\n\nBangladesh has [[List of countries and dependencies by population density|one of the highest population densities]] in the world. The total fertility rate (TFR) has been reduced by more than two thirds since Independence. Current TFR in Bangladesh is 2.1 which means that women have 2.1 children on average in their lifetime. At this TFR and without migration, country's population will eventually be neither growing nor shrinking, once the top of its age pyramid fills in.<ref>{{cite news |title=Healthy Change|url=https://www.dandc.eu/en/article/how-bangladesh-reduced-average-number-children-woman-mere-21|author=Najma Rizvi|website=Dandc.eu|date=16 June 2018 |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Population==\n[[File:Pyramide Bangladesh.PNG|thumb|left|Age-sex pyramid for Bangladesh, 2005]] The 2016 total population was {{UN Population|Bangladesh}} which makes Bangladesh the  [[List of countries and dependencies by population|eighth-most populous country]] in the world.\n\n===Census===\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://203.112.218.65/WebTestApplication/userfiles/Image/BBS/PHC2011Preliminary%20Result.pdf|title=2016 Population & Housing Census: Preliminary Results|website=203.112.218.65|accessdate=23 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120425161708/http://203.112.218.65/WebTestApplication/userfiles/Image/BBS/PHC2011Preliminary%20Result.pdf|archive-date=25 April 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n[[Image:Bangladesh population 1900to2010.svg|thumb|right|350px|Demographic evolution of the territory of Bangladesh (1900-2010).]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n'''Population of Bangladesh'''\n|-bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! Census date !! census population <br /> (thousands)!! adjusted population  <br />(thousands)\n|-\n|1901\n| 28 928\n|\n|-\n| 1911\n| 31 555\n|\n|-\n| 1921\n| 33 255\n|\n|-\n| 1931\n| 35 602\n|\n|-\n| 1941\n| 41 997\n|\n|-\n| 1951\n| 41 932\n|\n|-\n| 1961\n| 50 840\n|\n|-\n| 1974\n|  71 479\n|  76 398\n|-\n| 1981\n|  87 120\n|  89 912\n|-\n| 1991\n| 106 313\n| 111 455\n|-\n| 2001\n| 124 355\n| 130 523\n|-\n| 15 Mar 2011\n|  142 319\n|152 518\n|}\n\np=provisional figure\n\n===UN estimates<ref name=\"WPP 2017\">{{cite web |url=http://esa.un.org/unpd/wpp/index.htm |title=Wo